  'manager.setup.issnDescription' => 'The ISSN (International Standard Serial Number) is an eight-digit number which identifies periodical publications as such, including electronic serials. It is managed by a world wide network of National Centres coordinated by an International Centre based in Paris, backed by Unesco and the French Government. A number can be obtained from the <a href="http://www.issn.org" target="_blank">ISSN web site</a>.  This can be done at any point in operating the journal.',
